Package soot.jimple.infoflow.android.entryPointCreators

Class AndroidEntryPointCreator

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.entryPointCreators.BaseEntryPointCreator
      • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.entryPointCreators.AbstractAndroidEntryPointCreator
        • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.entryPointCreators.AndroidEntryPointCreator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEntryPointCreator
    public class AndroidEntryPointCreator
extends AbstractAndroidEntryPointCreator
implements IEntryPointCreator
    class which creates a dummy main method with the entry points according to the Android lifecycles based on: http://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Activity.html#ActivityLifecycle and http://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Service.html and http://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/BroadcastReceiver.html#ReceiverLifecycle and http://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/BroadcastReceiver.html and https://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Fragment.html
    Author:
    Christian, Steven Arzt

        Sets the list of callback functions to be integrated into the Android lifecycle
        Parameters:
        callbackFunctions - The list of callback functions to be integrated into the Android lifecycle. This is a mapping from the Android element class (activity, service, etc.) to the list of callback methods for that element.
